			<div class="content" id="post-content-4674372">
									

<p>The Seminars Team is currently searching for new Junior Staff members.</p>
<p><strong>Primary Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Organizing and/or hosting seminars and workshops</li>
<li>Moderating seminars and workshops (including orientations)</li>
<li>Revising lesson plans</li>
<li>Providing input and new perspectives for developing seminars</li>
<li>Advertising seminars and workshops</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Secondary Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Taking notes on seminars as they occur</li>
<li>Condensing seminar notes for public consumption</li>
<li>Keeping Seminars Team resources (hub, official sandbox, forum threads, etc) up to date</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Competitive Perks:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>An experience of staff ongoings, including policy discussions and other shenanigans</li>
<li>The ability to post to the staff site. You won't be responsible for voting or anything but can give your view on policies relevant to Community Outreach.</li>
<li>After ~4 months on the team, we are able to nominate you for promotion to fully Operational Staff (which occurs every 4 months). (Note: If we choose not to nominate you, and you're curious why, we will try to be completely open with you about it.)</li>
<li>No pressure- if it's not for you, there's nothing forcing you to keep at it.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>PLEASE NOTE:</strong> The Seminars Team is still new, rapidly growing, and responsibilities and the needs of the team are still changing and expanding. Joining this team allows for the opportunity for you to not only gain responsibility but present new ideas to the team. <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Being on the Seminars team might require you to interact with high-level staff in a one-on-one setting. Please be aware of this.</span></p>
<p><strong>If you're interested, please REPLY TO THIS POST with answers to the following questions:</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>Why do you want to be on JS for Community Outreach (specifically Seminars Team) and why are you a good fit?</p>
<p>How active are you, both on the site and on the chat?</p>
<p>How can we contact you (IRC/WikiDot/Discord)?</p>
</blockquote>

