<p>I love helping out everywhere, mostly I can be seen in Discords and #thecritters helping crit drafts, and giving advice on ideas. Despite being relatively new to SCP stuff I'm already working on my 3rd article and my 4th tale. (I've been active around 6 months.) I understand that the team works really hard to help people with their writing and I would love to become a part of that. Besides, we should always be looking to help others and lift them up right? I want to help guide newer writers into the swing of things as well as make this community a better place for everyone.</p>
<p>We are kind of a mix of all types of creative media if you think about it, and I come from a very well versed place in it with art, writing, music, and other wise so I feel that I can help in that aspect. Part of the job is both living up to the standards of previous/active staff and helping found new ones. I believe I am up for that challenge.</p>
<p>With that, I have had experience both writing and revising lesson plans and helping people learn things as a teachers aid and as band leadership (Uniforms, section leader, pit music tech, and librarian), thus I think this role would suit me well.</p>
