<h4><span>Why do you want to be on JS for Community Outreach (specifically Seminars Team) and why are you a good fit?</span></h4>
<p>I'd like to join Seminars Team because I love interacting with the community surrounding SCP. From the new peeps who have just joined to those that have been here so long they can apply for a pension, I love meeting new people and introducing them into the community.</p>
<p>I've been on the Swamp Critters for some time already so I have experience with interacting with both new and older users from the position of a &quot;more experienced other&quot;. Additionally, I'm voiced in #thecritters on IRC and frequently give critique on all sorts of articles from SCPs to Tales, from grammar to structural content.</p>
<p>Finally, I'd really enjoy being on the Seminars Team as it allows me to more frequently engage with the community. I feel like I have plenty of knowledge to share with other users having studied the English Language and being a current student of History at university.</p>
<h3><span>How active are you, both on the site and on the chat?</span></h3>
<p>I'm very active on the chat. I'm typically online for hours either talking or critiquing other users. On the site, I occasionally browse the wiki to post in the ideas and drafts threads, especially when users contact me via wikidot pms.</p>
